1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:02,670
♪

2
00:00:14,013 --> 00:00:17,725
You don't know what you'll be
until you've grown up.

3
00:00:17,726 --> 00:00:21,605
So, is it the same for witches?

4
00:00:26,819 --> 00:00:28,863
[footsteps]

5
00:00:45,587 --> 00:00:47,505
[Coco sighs]

6
00:00:47,506 --> 00:00:49,132
[wind blowing]

7
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:53,554
[Coco exclaims]

8
00:01:19,162 --> 00:01:20,455
[sighs tiredly]

9
00:01:21,080 --> 00:01:23,666
Oh! I'm making
a big mess, aren't I?

10
00:01:23,667 --> 00:01:25,711
Sorry, I'm almost done.

11
00:01:28,714 --> 00:01:31,173
Don't worry,
it'll go back to normal.

12
00:01:31,174 --> 00:01:34,386
This spring is touched
by magic!

13
00:01:58,493 --> 00:02:00,703
I'll never get tired of it.

14
00:02:00,704 --> 00:02:03,749
Magic is so... amazing!

15
00:02:07,086 --> 00:02:10,546
The world around us
is brimming with magic.

16
00:02:10,547 --> 00:02:14,550
A blessing that improves
our lives in so many ways.

17
00:02:14,978 --> 00:02:18,763
But how it works
is a bit of a mystery.

18
00:02:18,764 --> 00:02:22,308
The only ones who can
cast spells are witches.

19
00:02:22,309 --> 00:02:23,893
[cattle bleating]

20
00:02:23,894 --> 00:02:27,313
[COCO] All we ordinary people
can do is sit back

21
00:02:27,314 --> 00:02:29,565
and enjoy the results.

22
00:02:29,566 --> 00:02:32,360
But we can never use
magic ourselves.

23
00:02:34,696 --> 00:02:37,240
I wish I had been born a witch.

24
00:02:40,452 --> 00:02:41,620
Hm?

25
00:02:45,206 --> 00:02:47,207
Oh, sheets of white,

26
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:50,378
become now a cloak of flight!

27
00:02:52,798 --> 00:02:54,341
Uh...

28
00:02:54,842 --> 00:02:57,217
[gasps] No, come back!

29
00:02:57,218 --> 00:02:59,721
This isn't the kind
of flight I meant!

30
00:03:01,473 --> 00:03:03,307
[gasps]

31
00:03:03,308 --> 00:03:04,935
♪

32
00:03:08,105 --> 00:03:10,189
[exclaims softly]

33
00:03:12,191 --> 00:03:14,486
[Coco panting]

34
00:03:15,779 --> 00:03:17,990
A Pegasus Carriage!

35
00:03:18,824 --> 00:03:20,199
♪

36
00:03:20,659 --> 00:03:22,828
[exclaims excitedly]

37
00:03:30,669 --> 00:03:33,505
I've never seen one land!
I can't wait!

38
00:03:35,924 --> 00:03:37,341
Mom, look!

39
00:03:37,342 --> 00:03:39,052
There's a Pegasus Carriage!

40
00:03:39,053 --> 00:03:40,428
Mom!

41
00:03:42,181 --> 00:03:43,765
Mom, where are you?

42
00:03:44,474 --> 00:03:45,684
Mom?

43
00:03:46,601 --> 00:03:47,811
Oh...

44
00:03:48,896 --> 00:03:50,271
[BOTH] Huh?

45
00:03:51,106 --> 00:03:52,481
[QIFREY] Hm.

46
00:03:52,482 --> 00:03:54,734
I'm sorry, sir!
I didn't know you were there.

47
00:03:54,735 --> 00:03:56,276
It's quite all right.

48
00:03:56,277 --> 00:03:58,612
It was my own fault.
A poor place to stand.

49
00:03:58,613 --> 00:04:00,573
[WOMAN 1]
My word, I can't believe it!

50
00:04:00,574 --> 00:04:03,325
Imagine, finding such a garment
all the way out here!

51
00:04:03,326 --> 00:04:06,162
[WOMAN 2] Ah, yes, but isn't
wood-sorrel embroidery

52
00:04:06,163 --> 00:04:07,163
a tad dated?

53
00:04:07,164 --> 00:04:08,622
Oh, look at this!

54
00:04:08,623 --> 00:04:10,833
- Genuine Harrian lace!
- [both gasp]

55
00:04:10,834 --> 00:04:12,793
[WOMAN 2] Amazing! The stock
in the castle town

56
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:15,213
- sold out almost immediately.
- [Coco exclaims]

57
00:04:15,214 --> 00:04:16,714
- [indistinct chatter]
- It must have been them!

58
00:04:16,715 --> 00:04:19,133
They came
in the Pegasus Carriage!

59
00:04:19,134 --> 00:04:21,970
- [women chuckle]
- Oh. No, I'm not with them.

60
00:04:22,261 --> 00:04:25,347
Pardon me, but do you perhaps
have any more lace like this?

61
00:04:25,348 --> 00:04:26,432
[COCO'S MOM]
Oh, of course, ma'am.

62
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:28,350
I'll be right with you!

63
00:04:28,351 --> 00:04:30,686
Coco? I could use your help!

64
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:32,146
[WOMAN 3] How about this one?

65
00:04:32,147 --> 00:04:33,731
What can we do for you, sir?

66
00:04:33,732 --> 00:04:36,150
I was looking for some
smoke-colored fabric.

67
00:04:36,151 --> 00:04:37,651
But I can come again.

68
00:04:37,652 --> 00:04:39,486
I could cut it for you
if you like!

69
00:04:39,487 --> 00:04:40,738
Will you, now?

70
00:04:40,739 --> 00:04:42,531
You're in good hands with her!

71
00:04:42,532 --> 00:04:44,076
- I see.
- [indistinct chatter continues]

72
00:04:45,911 --> 00:04:47,745
[gasps excitedly]
When I'm done,

73
00:04:47,746 --> 00:04:49,663
can I go see
the Pegasus Carriage?

74
00:04:49,664 --> 00:04:51,082
Go see the what?

75
00:04:51,083 --> 00:04:53,167
There's a Pegasus Carriage
outside!

76
00:04:53,168 --> 00:04:54,460
Oh, for goodness' sake.

77
00:04:54,461 --> 00:04:55,753
We've talked about this.

78
00:04:55,754 --> 00:04:57,671
No meddling
with the customers' property.

79
00:04:57,672 --> 00:04:59,298
[COCO] I'll only look,
I promise!

80
00:04:59,507 --> 00:05:00,925
[Coco's mom sighs]

81
00:05:00,926 --> 00:05:02,635
[COCO] I'll stop talking about

82
00:05:02,636 --> 00:05:05,930
how I want to be a witch
all the time. Please?

83
00:05:05,931 --> 00:05:06,974
[COCO'S MOM] Mm...

84
00:05:07,348 --> 00:05:08,891
- [indistinct chatter continues]
- [Coco's mom sighs]

85
00:05:08,892 --> 00:05:11,393
All right, fine, but
only after you've finished.

86
00:05:11,394 --> 00:05:13,438
[gasps excitedly] Thank you.

87
00:05:14,231 --> 00:05:17,150
Sorry to keep you waiting!
What measurements did you need?

88
00:05:17,151 --> 00:05:19,902
- [QIFREY] Oh, here they are.
- I'll be right back.

89
00:05:19,903 --> 00:05:21,529
♪

90
00:05:33,792 --> 00:05:35,751
[inhales, blows softly]

91
00:05:35,752 --> 00:05:37,129
♪

92
00:05:42,176 --> 00:05:43,677
[sighs]

93
00:05:52,644 --> 00:05:53,854
[COCO] Uh?

94
00:05:57,565 --> 00:05:59,692
[Coco whimpers]

95
00:05:59,693 --> 00:06:00,861
My...

96
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:04,948
You have excellent focus
and steady hands.

97
00:06:05,657 --> 00:06:08,784
No hesitation in the line.
Clean cut.

98
00:06:08,785 --> 00:06:11,663
And a finish showing
precision and care.

99
00:06:12,039 --> 00:06:13,956
I had no idea
this village possessed

100
00:06:13,957 --> 00:06:15,542
such a skilled artisan.

101
00:06:16,751 --> 00:06:18,461
This is real magic.

102
00:06:18,712 --> 00:06:19,838
[Coco gasps]

103
00:06:20,172 --> 00:06:24,300
[shrieks] No! What I do here
isn't anything like magic!

104
00:06:24,301 --> 00:06:26,260
Magic is mysterious,
and priceless,

105
00:06:26,261 --> 00:06:28,012
and wonderfully shiny
and sparkly,

106
00:06:28,013 --> 00:06:30,014
and unbelievably beautiful!

107
00:06:30,015 --> 00:06:34,101
It's just so... so precious,

108
00:06:34,102 --> 00:06:36,436
more precious than I can say.

109
00:06:36,437 --> 00:06:39,606
Actually, come to think of it,
what am I saying?

110
00:06:39,607 --> 00:06:42,069
I'm getting the sense
you truly love magic.

111
00:06:44,529 --> 00:06:46,573
Why is that? Tell me.

112
00:06:47,448 --> 00:06:48,616
[Coco sighs]

113
00:06:51,912 --> 00:06:54,288
[COCO] When I was little,
my mother took me

114
00:06:54,289 --> 00:06:56,456
to a festival at the castle.

115
00:06:56,457 --> 00:06:57,917
And while I was there,

116
00:06:57,918 --> 00:07:00,544
I met a witch wearing a mask.

117
00:07:00,545 --> 00:07:02,172
[♪ mysterious music playing]

118
00:07:17,771 --> 00:07:19,773
[WITCH] You there, child.

119
00:07:20,315 --> 00:07:22,984
Would you like to buy
a magic picture book?

120
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:27,571
Magic?

121
00:07:27,572 --> 00:07:29,073
I love picture books,

122
00:07:29,074 --> 00:07:31,449
but I've never heard of magic.

123
00:07:31,450 --> 00:07:36,454
[WITCH] Why, magic is a miracle
that makes this world vibrant.

124
00:07:36,455 --> 00:07:39,166
A Pegasus Carriage in the sky,

125
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:42,460
a spring with waters
ever crystal clear.

126
00:07:42,461 --> 00:07:45,214
Even the cobblestones underfoot,

127
00:07:45,215 --> 00:07:47,967
glowing brightly with each step.

128
00:07:47,968 --> 00:07:50,719
All of these things are magic.

129
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,888
[gasps delightedly]

130
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:54,640
So pretty!

131
00:07:54,641 --> 00:07:56,892
Wow, magic is the best!

132
00:07:56,893 --> 00:07:58,685
Thank you, I love magic!

133
00:07:58,686 --> 00:08:01,314
[WITCH] Buy the book
and get this wand for free.

134
00:08:01,315 --> 00:08:02,690
♪

135
00:08:04,818 --> 00:08:07,569
Really? That's what you spent
the money on?

136
00:08:07,570 --> 00:08:10,656
I thought you wanted to get
some roasted strawberries.

137
00:08:10,657 --> 00:08:12,950
I did! But then
I followed a butterfly,

138
00:08:12,951 --> 00:08:15,161
and I found a person
wearing a pointed hat!

139
00:08:15,162 --> 00:08:17,455
Yes, so you told me
once already.

140
00:08:17,456 --> 00:08:20,207
And now, I have
a magic picture book!

141
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:21,625
And a wand too!

142
00:08:21,626 --> 00:08:23,044
[Coco's mom chuckles]

143
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:26,005
All right, then.
It's getting late, Coco,

144
00:08:26,006 --> 00:08:27,465
we should start heading home.

145
00:08:27,466 --> 00:08:29,175
- [COCO] Mommy!
- Hm?

146
00:08:29,176 --> 00:08:30,468
When I grow up,

147
00:08:30,469 --> 00:08:32,636
I'm going to become a witch
and use my magic

148
00:08:32,637 --> 00:08:34,888
to make the whole world vibrant,
just you wait!

149
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:36,474
You can't.

150
00:08:36,475 --> 00:08:38,018
But why not?

151
00:08:38,393 --> 00:08:42,855
Darling, you can't simply decide
to become a witch and use magic.

152
00:08:42,856 --> 00:08:45,774
It's a power
you have to be born with.

153
00:08:45,775 --> 00:08:48,402
Unfortunately, it's not
something ordinary people

154
00:08:48,403 --> 00:08:49,737
are capable of.

155
00:08:51,323 --> 00:08:53,573
Now, if you're ready,
let's go home.

156
00:08:53,574 --> 00:08:57,370
But look! The ground shines
wherever I step!

157
00:08:57,371 --> 00:08:58,412
[COCO'S MOM] Uh...

158
00:08:58,413 --> 00:09:00,498
[both chuckle]

159
00:09:00,499 --> 00:09:03,417
[COCO'S MOM] Well, let's see
if it keeps on shining

160
00:09:03,418 --> 00:09:05,169
all the way home.

161
00:09:05,170 --> 00:09:08,464
If so, maybe
you can use magic.

162
00:09:08,465 --> 00:09:09,757
[Coco exclaims softly]

163
00:09:17,516 --> 00:09:20,684
Ever since, it's been my dream
to become a witch,

164
00:09:20,685 --> 00:09:22,353
and I can't seem to let it go.

165
00:09:22,354 --> 00:09:24,980
I'd be interested in hearing
a bit more about the...

166
00:09:24,981 --> 00:09:26,066
[loud thud]

167
00:09:26,816 --> 00:09:28,859
- [WOMAN 3] Oh, my...
- [WOMAN 2] What was that?

168
00:09:28,860 --> 00:09:29,903
[COCO'S MOM] Coco?

169
00:09:30,237 --> 00:09:32,738
- [MAN] Whoa there, settle down.
- [horses neighing]

170
00:09:32,739 --> 00:09:35,450
Steady. Steady!

171
00:09:37,494 --> 00:09:39,245
[all gasp]

172
00:09:39,246 --> 00:09:41,706
[cattle bleating]

173
00:09:44,251 --> 00:09:46,835
Great, now look what you did.

174
00:09:46,836 --> 00:09:48,504
[TANERL] Shut up. Ow...

175
00:09:48,505 --> 00:09:49,755
[COCO] Are you all right?

176
00:09:49,756 --> 00:09:51,382
- Coco.
- [COCO] What happened?

177
00:09:51,383 --> 00:09:54,134
We didn't do anything.
It just suddenly fell apart.

178
00:09:54,135 --> 00:09:55,344
No, it didn't, liar!

179
00:09:55,345 --> 00:09:57,471
It fell because you crawled
underneath it!

180
00:09:57,472 --> 00:09:58,638
[TANERL] You snitch!

181
00:09:58,639 --> 00:10:00,140
He hit his head
while he was down there.

182
00:10:00,141 --> 00:10:01,350
And it fell over.

183
00:10:01,351 --> 00:10:03,352
[WOMAN 3]
No! This is absolutely terrible!

184
00:10:03,353 --> 00:10:04,811
- [gasping]
- What have you done

185
00:10:04,812 --> 00:10:05,938
to our Pegasus Carriage?

186
00:10:05,939 --> 00:10:08,232
[WOMAN 2]
It belongs to my father!

187
00:10:08,233 --> 00:10:09,567
We are so sorry!

188
00:10:09,568 --> 00:10:11,944
I'm sure these boys feel awful
for troubling you.

189
00:10:11,945 --> 00:10:13,946
How does your apology help us?

190
00:10:13,947 --> 00:10:16,365
Without a carriage,
we can't return home!

191
00:10:16,366 --> 00:10:18,243
[COCO'S MOM]
Oh, dear me, what can we do?

192
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:20,412
[QIFREY] Pardon me.

193
00:10:22,539 --> 00:10:24,165
Perhaps I could be of service.

194
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:26,460
I took a look,

195
00:10:26,585 --> 00:10:28,877
and the damage doesn't appear
to be serious.

196
00:10:28,878 --> 00:10:31,088
Really? And who are you?

197
00:10:31,089 --> 00:10:35,135
Apologies, allow me
to cap off my attire.

198
00:10:36,511 --> 00:10:37,678
[Coco gasps]

199
00:10:39,556 --> 00:10:40,889
[gasps]

200
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:44,519
Qifrey the witch,
at your service, madam.

201
00:10:47,272 --> 00:10:49,607
[BOTH] A pointed hat.

202
00:10:49,608 --> 00:10:50,942
You can fix it, then?

203
00:10:51,234 --> 00:10:52,485
[QIFREY] Indeed.

204
00:10:52,486 --> 00:10:54,736
[MAN] You certainly are
a lifesaver, Sir Witch!

205
00:10:54,737 --> 00:10:55,988
[QIFREY]
It's nothing at all.

206
00:10:55,989 --> 00:10:57,948
Why, I'll simply need to reapply
the spell

207
00:10:57,949 --> 00:10:59,283
to the floorboard
of the carriage.

208
00:10:59,284 --> 00:11:01,494
Your help is appreciated!

209
00:11:01,495 --> 00:11:03,245
And happily given!

210
00:11:03,246 --> 00:11:05,205
However, this work
environment is a bit...

211
00:11:05,206 --> 00:11:06,540
You can use our workshop,
we would be

212
00:11:06,541 --> 00:11:08,208
- so honored and delighted!
- Coco!

213
00:11:08,209 --> 00:11:10,545
What? We would, Mom,
wouldn't we?

214
00:11:12,172 --> 00:11:16,134
I mean, he's an honest
to goodness witch.

215
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:20,012
This could be the chance
I've been waiting for,

216
00:11:20,013 --> 00:11:23,891
to witness the very moment
a spell is cast!

217
00:11:27,770 --> 00:11:29,564
[cattle bleating]

218
00:11:32,442 --> 00:11:34,276
May I ask for your assistance?

219
00:11:34,277 --> 00:11:36,278
I will need someone
to keep watch,

220
00:11:36,279 --> 00:11:38,030
so I can cast
the spell in private.

221
00:11:38,031 --> 00:11:41,408
No one must come in
under any circumstances.

222
00:11:41,409 --> 00:11:42,619
Thank you.

223
00:11:45,163 --> 00:11:47,666
Guess it was too much
to hope for.

224
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:51,628
Still, why can't we see
how it's done?

225
00:11:52,546 --> 00:11:55,713
Magic is practiced
all over the world,

226
00:11:55,714 --> 00:11:59,009
yet most of us don't have
the first clue how it happens.

227
00:11:59,010 --> 00:12:01,846
Only witches know the secret.

228
00:12:02,305 --> 00:12:04,349
The secret... Oh?

229
00:12:10,063 --> 00:12:12,940
- [COCO] Where'd they go?
- [TANERL] Almost fell!

230
00:12:13,608 --> 00:12:16,485
[gasps] What do you two think
you're doing?

231
00:12:16,486 --> 00:12:17,487
[KAMLA] She caught us!

232
00:12:17,654 --> 00:12:19,154
[TANERL] She doesn't matter.
We're fine.

233
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:21,408
Can we see into the room
from here?

234
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,951
- [COCO] Wait for me!
- Fine, but keep your voice down!

235
00:12:24,952 --> 00:12:26,496
[COCO] Out of the way!

236
00:12:34,087 --> 00:12:35,589
[all exclaim]

237
00:12:38,883 --> 00:12:41,009
Man, talk about disappointing.

238
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:42,470
What a letdown.

239
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:46,182
[wind howling]

240
00:12:48,685 --> 00:12:51,396
[Coco whimpers] What is this?

241
00:12:52,188 --> 00:12:53,398
[Coco gasps]

242
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:59,613
[wind howling]

243
00:13:17,547 --> 00:13:18,923
[Coco gasps]

244
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:23,801
[COCO] I shouldn't!

245
00:13:23,802 --> 00:13:27,056
But I really want to!
But I shouldn't!

246
00:13:36,775 --> 00:13:38,192
[gasps softly]

247
00:13:45,575 --> 00:13:47,702
♪

248
00:13:50,913 --> 00:13:52,165
[Coco gasps softly]

249
00:13:54,833 --> 00:13:56,419
[COCO] He's drawing.

250
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:02,675
Drawing magic?

251
00:14:02,676 --> 00:14:04,135
With a pen?

252
00:14:04,678 --> 00:14:07,221
The wand that I got that day.

253
00:14:07,681 --> 00:14:09,349
Was it actually...

254
00:14:11,058 --> 00:14:12,727
I see now.

255
00:14:13,353 --> 00:14:16,271
Witches don't cast spells.

256
00:14:16,272 --> 00:14:18,024
They draw them!

257
00:14:19,651 --> 00:14:21,026
[QIFREY] That's that.

258
00:14:21,027 --> 00:14:23,321
Coco, all finished here.

259
00:14:28,785 --> 00:14:30,869
[Coco panting]

260
00:14:31,412 --> 00:14:32,579
Coco?

261
00:14:32,580 --> 00:14:35,709
[COCO] Oh, are you done?
[panting]

262
00:14:37,669 --> 00:14:39,086
[horses neighing]

263
00:14:44,384 --> 00:14:46,427
[bird squawking]

264
00:14:50,390 --> 00:14:51,807
[Coco's mom sighs]

265
00:14:51,808 --> 00:14:54,434
You know, I was starting
to worry there for a moment.

266
00:14:54,435 --> 00:14:55,436
[COCO] Uh?

267
00:14:55,812 --> 00:14:58,231
[COCO'S MOM]
Well, you're in love with magic.

268
00:14:58,690 --> 00:15:01,107
You have been ever since
you were little.

269
00:15:01,108 --> 00:15:03,151
So I thought you might ask
to leave home

270
00:15:03,152 --> 00:15:05,196
- and go off with that witch.
- [Coco gasps]

271
00:15:06,239 --> 00:15:08,448
[COCO'S MOM] I already lost
your father to illness.

272
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:11,284
If I had to face
losing you too,

273
00:15:11,285 --> 00:15:12,952
I don't know what I'd do.

274
00:15:12,953 --> 00:15:14,496
You never will, Mom!

275
00:15:14,497 --> 00:15:16,875
I promise I won't ever
leave you all alone!

276
00:15:20,086 --> 00:15:23,129
[COCO'S MOM] My goodness,
aren't you a sweet girl.

277
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:24,257
Thank you.

278
00:15:30,597 --> 00:15:31,638
[COCO'S MOM] Hm?

279
00:15:31,639 --> 00:15:33,391
- Mm... [chuckles]
- [giggles]

280
00:15:37,687 --> 00:15:39,021
[both sigh]

281
00:15:42,024 --> 00:15:43,483
Goodnight, Mom.

282
00:15:43,484 --> 00:15:45,152
[COCO'S MOM] Goodnight, dear.

283
00:15:45,570 --> 00:15:47,280
- Oh, Coco?
- Hm?

284
00:15:49,490 --> 00:15:50,990
Never mind.

285
00:15:50,991 --> 00:15:52,159
Sweet dreams.

286
00:15:52,744 --> 00:15:54,287
You too.

287
00:16:01,419 --> 00:16:02,628
[Coco sighs softly]

288
00:16:02,629 --> 00:16:04,463
I thought you might ask
to leave home

289
00:16:04,464 --> 00:16:05,881
and go off with that witch.

290
00:16:05,882 --> 00:16:07,300
[Coco sighs]

291
00:16:23,775 --> 00:16:26,319
[COCO] The patterns
in the picture book,

292
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:29,489
the free wand
that came with it...

293
00:16:30,573 --> 00:16:33,366
They were more than
they seemed.

294
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:35,745
This is a magic pen!

295
00:16:38,665 --> 00:16:40,667
[creaking]

296
00:16:47,924 --> 00:16:49,633
[COCO] Forgive me, Mom.

297
00:16:49,634 --> 00:16:51,552
I won't go anywhere, but...

298
00:16:52,010 --> 00:16:54,180
I have to try it!

299
00:17:12,866 --> 00:17:15,368
[pen scratching]

300
00:17:23,125 --> 00:17:25,419
♪

301
00:17:37,390 --> 00:17:39,141
[Coco breathes shakily]

302
00:17:41,352 --> 00:17:43,186
[soft jingling]

303
00:17:43,187 --> 00:17:44,438
[COCO] Huh?

304
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:49,192
[groans] Nothing happened.

305
00:17:49,193 --> 00:17:50,777
Now that I think about it,

306
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:53,030
of course it wouldn't be
that easy.

307
00:17:53,031 --> 00:17:54,407
♪

308
00:18:05,251 --> 00:18:06,419
[Coco gasps]

309
00:18:08,128 --> 00:18:09,881
[exclaims]

310
00:18:11,257 --> 00:18:12,425
[gasps]

311
00:18:13,133 --> 00:18:14,761
[exclaims]

312
00:18:18,932 --> 00:18:21,433
[COCO] It sparkled!
That must mean it worked!

313
00:18:21,434 --> 00:18:23,100
I can't believe it!
I used magic!

314
00:18:23,101 --> 00:18:26,605
I used actual,
real-life magic! [squealing]

315
00:18:26,606 --> 00:18:28,147
So magic is drawn.

316
00:18:28,148 --> 00:18:29,608
But I wasn't supposed
to see it!

317
00:18:29,609 --> 00:18:32,236
Will I get into trouble
if he finds out?

318
00:18:36,783 --> 00:18:38,576
Maybe I'll draw...

319
00:18:38,952 --> 00:18:41,078
just one more.

320
00:18:41,079 --> 00:18:42,371
♪

321
00:18:53,549 --> 00:18:56,970
[QIFREY] A picture book.
How curious.

322
00:18:57,595 --> 00:18:59,973
Why does it nag at me so?

323
00:19:01,808 --> 00:19:04,477
[gasps] Could it be?

324
00:19:06,437 --> 00:19:07,729
[Coco gasps] A fire spell!

325
00:19:07,730 --> 00:19:09,857
Please stop burning,
please stop burning!

326
00:19:11,067 --> 00:19:13,486
[sighs] That was too close.

327
00:19:14,695 --> 00:19:15,738
And yet...

328
00:19:17,406 --> 00:19:19,700
I think I'm starting
to get the hang of it.

329
00:19:20,326 --> 00:19:23,453
Bigger ones are more powerful
than smaller ones.

330
00:19:23,454 --> 00:19:27,164
And neatly drawn ones
last longer than sloppy ones.

331
00:19:27,165 --> 00:19:31,044
But drawing them that big
and that neat isn't easy.

332
00:19:31,045 --> 00:19:34,089
Although he certainly
made it look that way.

333
00:19:34,090 --> 00:19:35,340
I know!

334
00:19:35,341 --> 00:19:36,550
♪

335
00:19:40,138 --> 00:19:41,596
[COCO] I was right.

336
00:19:41,597 --> 00:19:43,098
It's a lot easier to be neat

337
00:19:43,099 --> 00:19:45,518
when I trace the drawing
rather than copy it.

338
00:19:54,485 --> 00:19:56,320
And done!

339
00:19:56,863 --> 00:19:58,114
[Coco gasps]

340
00:19:59,281 --> 00:20:01,575
♪

341
00:20:15,339 --> 00:20:16,589
[Coco gasps]

342
00:20:16,590 --> 00:20:18,008
[QIFREY] What did you draw?

343
00:20:18,009 --> 00:20:19,551
Tell me, Coco!

344
00:20:19,552 --> 00:20:21,136
What spell did you draw?

345
00:20:21,137 --> 00:20:22,762
I... I don't know.

346
00:20:22,763 --> 00:20:24,848
I traced a pattern
from the book, and I...

347
00:20:24,849 --> 00:20:26,184
- [COCO'S MOM] Coco?
- [Coco gasps]

348
00:20:27,225 --> 00:20:28,476
[gasps]

349
00:20:28,477 --> 00:20:29,603
[COCO] Mom?

350
00:20:33,566 --> 00:20:35,567
Coco!

351
00:20:35,568 --> 00:20:37,485
Mom, run!

352
00:20:37,486 --> 00:20:39,780
[Coco's mom gasps, screams]

353
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:44,785
No, this isn't real.

354
00:20:45,119 --> 00:20:46,828
[cries] Mom!

355
00:20:46,829 --> 00:20:48,205
Mom!

356
00:20:48,206 --> 00:20:50,999
- Mom! Mom!
- [QIFREY] Forbidden magic!

357
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:53,459
- Let go! I have to save my mom!
- Hold still!

358
00:20:53,460 --> 00:20:55,795
- She's in danger because of me!
- I don't want to drop you!

359
00:20:55,796 --> 00:20:56,922
[QIFREY] Stop it!

360
00:20:56,923 --> 00:20:59,800
That spell is evil,
you mustn't... No!

361
00:21:04,722 --> 00:21:06,347
- [Coco cries]
- [QIFREY] Coco!

362
00:21:06,348 --> 00:21:08,516
[COCO] I'm here, Mom!

363
00:21:08,517 --> 00:21:10,853
[wails] No!

364
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:12,855
♪

365
00:21:14,607 --> 00:21:16,859
[cries] I'm sorry.

366
00:21:17,693 --> 00:21:19,112
I didn't know.

367
00:21:19,695 --> 00:21:21,404
[QIFREY] Of course you didn't.

368
00:21:21,405 --> 00:21:24,575
It was all kept a secret
to prevent tragedies like this.

369
00:21:25,201 --> 00:21:28,995
A special ink,
and a set of Casting Seals.

370
00:21:28,996 --> 00:21:31,915
That's all one needs
for magic to be used.

371
00:21:31,916 --> 00:21:34,627
Concealing that is
our One Great Rule.

372
00:21:35,377 --> 00:21:37,087
And now that
you know the truth,

373
00:21:37,088 --> 00:21:39,881
you must have
your memories erased.

374
00:21:39,882 --> 00:21:42,176
[Coco gasps, cries]

375
00:21:43,052 --> 00:21:46,012
Please don't! I can't forget.

376
00:21:46,013 --> 00:21:48,014
If I do, then who'll save
my mom?

377
00:21:48,015 --> 00:21:50,475
I'm afraid I couldn't say.

378
00:21:50,476 --> 00:21:53,103
I don't know
what kind of magic it was,

379
00:21:53,104 --> 00:21:55,981
but I can remember
all those drawings by heart!

380
00:21:55,982 --> 00:21:59,109
And if all those memories
are lost, then my mom...

381
00:21:59,110 --> 00:22:01,112
[Qifrey gasps] The picture book.

382
00:22:01,487 --> 00:22:02,862
That's right.

383
00:22:02,863 --> 00:22:04,990
If it came
from who I think it did,

384
00:22:04,991 --> 00:22:07,826
then I finally have a link
to their whereabouts!

385
00:22:07,827 --> 00:22:09,995
This girl's memories
are my only chance

386
00:22:09,996 --> 00:22:11,830
to track them down!

387
00:22:11,831 --> 00:22:14,166
You say you remember
the book by heart?

388
00:22:14,167 --> 00:22:15,416
[COCO] Hm.

389
00:22:15,417 --> 00:22:17,710
[QIFREY] And you recall
the page you copied?

390
00:22:17,711 --> 00:22:18,879
[COCO] Hmm.

391
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:22,548
[gasps] If we had
the book I used,

392
00:22:22,549 --> 00:22:25,343
I could show you
which seal I drew.

393
00:22:26,304 --> 00:22:28,930
If we can find the one
that hurt my Mom,

394
00:22:28,931 --> 00:22:31,309
do you think there's something
you could do for her?

395
00:22:33,894 --> 00:22:36,689
[QIFREY] There is a chance.

396
00:22:37,898 --> 00:22:41,693
[Coco cries] Mr. Qifrey,
please don't erase my memories!

397
00:22:41,694 --> 00:22:45,656
I'm willing to do anything
to rescue my mother!

398
00:22:47,407 --> 00:22:49,284
Will you keep our secret?

399
00:22:49,285 --> 00:22:50,911
[COCO] I promise!

400
00:22:51,954 --> 00:22:53,746
And are you willing to learn?

401
00:22:53,747 --> 00:22:55,749
To learn... [gasps]

402
00:22:56,250 --> 00:22:59,211
[QIFREY] Once you know
the truth, it cannot be undone.

403
00:22:59,212 --> 00:23:02,756
And so, you must join
those trusted with the secret.

404
00:23:03,299 --> 00:23:06,844
That is your way forward,
the only way.

405
00:23:08,346 --> 00:23:11,891
- Coco, from now on...
- [gasps]

406
00:23:12,390 --> 00:23:15,019
You will be a witch.

